content:
Certainly! Here's a simple HTML page that includes a quiz about the three branches of the United States government. The page also provides a brief overview of each branch.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>US Government Branches Quiz</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .feedback {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
    <script>
        function checkAnswers() {
            let correct = 0;

            // Check first question
            if (document.querySelector('input[name="q1"]:checked')?.value === "Executive") {
                document.getElementById("feedback1").textContent = "Correct!";
                correct++;
            } else {
                document.getElementById("feedback1").textContent = "Incorrect, the correct answer is Executive.";
            }

            // Check second question
            if (document.querySelector('input[name="q2"]:checked')?.value === "Legislative") {
                document.getElementById("feedback2").textContent = "Correct!";
                correct++;
            } else {
                document.getElementById("feedback2").textContent = "Incorrect, the correct answer is Legislative.";
            }

            // Check third question
            if (document.querySelector('input[name="q3"]:checked')?.value === "Judicial") {
                document.getElementById("feedback3").textContent = "Correct!";
                correct++;
            } else {
                document.getElementById("feedback3").textContent = "Incorrect, the correct answer is Judicial.";
            }

            alert("You got " + correct + " out of 3 correct!");
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Quiz: Three Branches of the United States Government</h1>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The United States government is divided into three branches:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Executive Branch</strong>: Responsible for enforcing laws; headed by the President.</li>
        <li><strong>Legislative Branch</strong>: Responsible for making laws; consists of the Congress (Senate and House of Representatives).</li>
        <li><strong>Judicial Branch</strong>: Responsible for interpreting laws; headed by the Supreme Court.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Quiz</h2>

    <form id="quizForm">
        <div>
            <p>1. Which branch of the government is responsible for enforcing laws?</p>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="Executive"> Executive</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="Legislative"> Legislative</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="Judicial"> Judicial</label><br>
            <p class="feedback" id="feedback1"></p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <p>2. Which branch of the government is responsible for making laws?</p>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="Executive"> Executive</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="Legislative"> Legislative</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="Judicial"> Judicial</label><br>
            <p class="feedback" id="feedback2"></p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <p>3. Which branch of the government is responsible for interpreting laws?</p>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="Executive"> Executive</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="Legislative"> Legislative</label><br>
            <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="Judicial"> Judicial</label><br>
            <p class="feedback" id="feedback3"></p>
        </div>

        <button type="button" onclick="checkAnswers()">Submit Answers</button>
    </form>

</body>
</html>
```

This HTML page contains a brief overview of the three branches of the U.S. government followed by a quiz. The quiz consists of three multiple-choice questions, each with feedback on whether the answer is correct or incorrect. The user receives an alert with their total score after submitting their answers.
